  "question": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?",
  "prompt": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "160",
  "generated_text": "To find the total time required for Carla to download the file, we need to break the process into two phases: the initial download and the restart/re-download.\n\n**Phase 1: Initial Download**\n*   **Total file size:** $200 \\text{ GB}$\n*   **Download speed:** $2 \\text{ GB/minute}$\n*   **Time taken:** $\\frac{200 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 100 \\text{ minutes}$\n*   **Time remaining:** At 40% completion, the time elapsed is $40\\%$ of $100$ minutes.\n    $$0.40 \\times 100 = 40 \\text{ minutes}$$\n*   **Remaining data:** $60\\%$ of the file.\n    $$0.60 \\times 200 = 120 \\text{ GB}$$\n\n**Phase 2: Restart and Re-download**\n*   **Restart time:** $20 \\text{ minutes}$\n*   **Download speed:** $2 \\text{ GB/minute}$ (assumed constant)\n*   **Time taken:** $\\frac{120 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 60 \\text{ minutes}$\n\n**Total Time Calculation**\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = \\text{Phase 1 Time} + \\text{Restart Time} + \\text{Phase 2 Time} $$\n$$ \\text{Total Time} = 100 + 20 + 60 = 180 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\nThe total time to download the file is 180 minutes.\n\n\\boxed{180}\n",
